						               													<description>Tournez man&amp;egrave;ge is a mutual knowledge game inspired by a French TV game from the 80s. The board is a 3D carrousel.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game takes place in two parts: making the teams then the determination of the level of affinity. The team with the highest level of affinity wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To make the teams, each player draws a question card. The carousel is launched and the player facing the side with the highest number becomes the playmaker. He asks the 8 questions on his card. Each question has 4 possible answers. The player to his left places a token of his color face down to indicate his answer in the corresponding box. Each player will do the same. The player of the game then collects all the tokens corresponding to his own choices. When all the players have been playmakers, the player with the most chips can choose his teammate. The second player with the most chips will in turn choose and so on&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the second phase of the game, players test their affinity level. They secretly choose photos of objects while imagining the choice of their teammate. The choice is indicated in the same way as for the teams: a colored token is placed on the corresponding space in the carousel. They will earn points when the choices are the same. The team with the most points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
